<p>i have a stored procedure that copies an existing excel file and renames it, then I export data from sql server to the new excel file.  This works!  My issue is that one of the columns needs to be right align and in a number format.  How can I do this?</p>  <p>Here is the tsql:</p>  <pre><code>/* Build date string MMddyyyy */ DECLARE @DateString AS NVARCHaR(8) DECLARE @Today AS DateTime SET @Today = GetDate() SET @DateString = CONVERT(NVARCHAR(2),MONTH(@Today)) + CONVERT(NVARCHAR(2),DAY(@Today)) + CONVERT(NVARCHAR(4),YEAR(@Today))  /* build copy command */ DECLARE @Cmd AS NVARCHAR(255) DECLARE @SourceFile AS NVARCHAR(255) DECLARE @DestinationFile AS NVARCHAR(255) SET @SourceFile = 'C:\temp\TeamCurrentStockInventory_template.xlsx' SET @DestinationFile = 'C:\temp\TeamCurrentStockInventory_' + @DateString + '.xlsx' SET @Cmd = 'COPY "' + @SourceFile + '" "' + @DestinationFile + '"';    /* execute copy command */   EXEC xp_cmdshell @Cmd;    /* Insert data into the copied excel file */ DECLARE @Sql AS NVARCHAR(MAX) SET @Sql = N'INSERT INTO             OPENROWSET(''Microsoft.ACE.OLEDB.12.0'',             ''Excel 12.0;Database=' + @DestinationFile + ';HDR=YES'',             ''SELECT Item, Description, Category, Location, Sublocation, Quantity, Comments FROM [Sheet1$]'')      SELECT      VIEW_CurrentStock_1.ItemName AS Item, VIEW_CurrentStock_1.ItemDescription AS Description,                 BASE_Category_1.Name AS Category, BASE_Location_1.Name AS Location,                 VIEW_CurrentStock_1.Sublocation AS Sublocaiton, CONVERT(INTEGER, VIEW_CurrentStock_1.Quantity) AS Quantity,                 VIEW_CurrentStock_1.Custom1 AS Comments                      FROM        [DBServer].inFlow.dbo.BASE_Location AS BASE_Location_1 INNER JOIN                 [DBServer].inFlow.dbo.VIEW_CurrentStock AS VIEW_CurrentStock_1 INNER JOIN                 [DBServer].inFlow.dbo.BASE_Category AS BASE_Category_1 ON VIEW_CurrentStock_1.CategoryId = BASE_Category_1.CategoryId ON BASE_Location_1.LocationId = VIEW_CurrentStock_1.LocationId     ORDER BY    VIEW_CurrentStock_1.ProdId'  --PRINT @Sql EXEC(@Sql) </code></pre>